# get_logs  (category: diagnostics)

Get ComfyUI server runtime logs. Useful for debugging execution errors, model loading issues, missing nodes, and Python tracebacks.

Parameters (JSON Schema):
{
 "type": "object",
 "properties": {
  "max_lines": {
   "description": "Maximum number of log lines to return from the end (default: 100)",
   "type": "integer",
   "minimum": 1,
   "maximum": 2000
  },
  "keyword": {
   "description": "Filter log lines containing this keyword (case-insensitive). Examples: 'error', 'warning', 'VRAM', a node name",
   "type": "string"
  }
 }
}

Run it with: call_tool {"name": "get_logs", "args": {...}}
